The paper presents a control method for a ground vehicle, which involves modeling unknown dynamics using Bayesian Linear Regression and using a stochastic Model Predictive Controller. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques such as Bayesian Linear Regression and Gaussian Process Regression suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with control systems and adaptation to changing operating conditions, which suggests that it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of a stereo camera for localization suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the use of predictive learning control suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
